event.title: now the northern parts of the Hundred of Clinton, W. & A. Rogers leased

data.event: In 1854 in what is now the northern parts of the Hundred of Clinton, W. & A. Rogers leased 75 square miles at an annual rental of ten shillings per square mile.

event.title: 1860, near the centre of the Hundred, T. & W. Day leased

data.event: In 1860, near the centre of the Hundred, T. & W. Day leased twelve square miles.
Clinton began a gradual decline after 1878 when the railway between Wallaroo and Adelaide was completed.
